WHAT IS THE SPOTIFY MODEL?

The Spotify model is an approach for scaling Agile that emphasizes the importance of culture and network.

Note: Ever since its inception, this model was intended as more of an inspiration for organizations rather than a framework to be implemented as-is.

WHEN DID IT START?

It was first introduced back in 2012

However, it has continuously evolved since its original publication

WHY WAS IT CREATED?

The Spotify model arose as an Agile response to the issues that the company was facing at the time result of its rapid growth .

How to scale?

On what grounds?

How to balance coupling and alignment?

What kind of organization to build?

HOW DOES IT RELATE TO DANONE?

It lays the foundations for what an Agile organization could look like and sheds some light on how we could operate our Agile transformation at Danone.

SQUAD

Squads are the basic unit of development in an Agile organization.

    Characteristics:
  • Small (less than 10 people)
  • Cross-functional
  • Self-organizing
  • Has all the tools and competencies to fulfill its mission
    KEY ROLES:
  • PRODUCT OWNER
  • SCRUM MASTER/AGILE COACH
  • DEVELOPERS

  • He/She carries the vision of the product and is accountable for maximizing the value delivered.

  • He/She supports the team working in Agile, facilitates Agile events, and helps remove impediments.

  • They are responsible for delivering the expected value and they are empowered to determine how to fulfill their mission.

SQUAD

A group of squads that work on a related functional area is called a tribe.

It usually does not exceed 100 people.

A tribe can be seen as the
INCUBATOR
for the squad mini-startups.

In addition, tribes hold informal gatherings on a regular basis to discuss their work

Every tribe has a

Flip the cards to reveal a tribe leader's responsibilities

RESPONSIBILITIES

  • Provide a productive environment for the squads within the Tribe.

  • Share strategic insights to shed light on the tribe's mission and the squads' contribution.

  • Help squads with coordination and alignment.

Every chapter has a

CHAPTER

People from different squads who have similar skills and work within the same general competency area are grouped into Chapters.

Each chapter meets regularly to discuss their area of expertise and their specific challenges.

Flip the cards to reveal a tribe leader's responsibilities

Gather a community of squad members with comparable skills

Manage the people from their chapter

Help people grow the skills required to deliver the mission of their squads and tribe
